FBIS4-8845 "dreeu075_i_94005" FBIS-EEU-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues UN: Serbs Ignoring Cease-Fire AU1804181594 Paris AFP in English 1753 GMT 18 Apr 94 AU1804181594 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Sarajevo, April 18 (AFP) -- Serb forces pounded away at Gorazde Monday, ignoring their latest ceasefire announcement, the Red Cross and UN officials said. The UN peacekeeping force here reported tank, artillery and sniper fire on the mainly Moslem town in eastern Bosnia. Earlier in the day the United Nations said the Bosnian Serbs had agreed to an immediate ceasefire, the second in two days. Sunday's truce was ignored as well.
